    <p>To help you get services up and running as easily as possible, we’ve written the following deployment consideration guides so you can better understand what is required for a successful deployment:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p><a href="https://products.solace.com/products/10.6-Production/Documentation/Solace_Platform_HTML_Documentation_R1061/Cloud/Deployment-Considerations/deployment-architecture-azure.htm" class="link-offsite">Deploying PubSub+ Cloud with Azure </a>(This link directs you to a previous version of the help documentation because VM-based deployments have been deprecated)                </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><a href="https://products.solace.com/products/10.6-Production/Documentation/Solace_Platform_HTML_Documentation_R1061/Cloud/Deployment-Considerations/deployment-architecture-aws.htm" class="link-offsite">Deploying PubSub+ Cloud with AWS</a> (This link directs you to a previous version of the help documentation because VM-based deployments have been deprecated)
                </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Cloud/Deployment-Considerations/deployment-architecture-k8s.htm">Deploying PubSub+ Could with Kubernetes</MadCap:xref>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>These guides can be found in <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Cloud/Deployment-Considerations/deployment-architecture-k8s.htm">Deploying PubSub+ Event Broker: Cloud</MadCap:xref>. New guides will be posted as they become available. </p>
